dc_description_s: This data group represents public land survey system (PLSS) corners for Vilas County, Wisconsin in 2018 and includes the layers 'Vilas_PLSS_2018' [The current control point on the surface of the earth and its associated current coordinate value, generally determined by a surveying process and used to define an extremity of a boundary.]
uw_supplemental_s: This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2019. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2018. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2019. This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For the most current data for this county, please visit: https://data-vilas.opendata.arcgis.com/
